body:
A possible enhancement request. I am not sure if this is worth doing. [On this wrong code](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=d85313cb98b378d35495286fb7d5a0ef):

```rust
#![feature(const_option)]

use std::num::NonZeroU32;

trait HasNonZero {
    type NonZero;
}

impl HasNonZero for u32 {
    type NonZero = NonZeroU32;
}

fn main() {
    const _N: u32::NonZero =
        <u32 as HasNonZero>::NonZero::new(5).unwrap();
}
```

rustc 1.52.0-nightly gives:

```rust
error[E0223]: ambiguous associated type
  --> ...\test.rs:14:15
   |
14 |     const _N: u32::NonZero =
   |               ^^^^^^^^^^^^ help: use fully-qualified syntax: `<u32 as Trait>::NonZero`

error: aborting due to previous error
```

Instead of a generic `<u32 as Trait>::NonZero` rustc could suggest one (or few) likely traits like `<u32 as HasNonZero>::NonZero`.

